{
  "@@locale": "mr",
  "@@x-note": "मराठी / Marathi — INTENTIONALLY EMPTY. No message keys were added, and this is not an oversight. Nobody on this change is a Marathi speaker, and machine-translated or guessed copy shown to a low-literacy worker who is mid-OTP or mid-consent is WORSE than no translation: they cannot tell wrong copy from right copy, and the consent strings in particular carry DPDP meaning that a bad translation would misstate. Until a native speaker supplies real copy, gen-l10n fills every key from the TEMPLATE locale (app_hi.arb), so a Marathi build renders Hindi — readable Devanagari, correct meaning — instead of English or a blank. `flutter pub get` will print '\"mr\": N untranslated message(s).' every time; that warning is the point and is deliberately not suppressed. WHEN YOU TRANSLATE: add keys with the EXACT ids from app_hi.arb. A typo'd id is silently ignored by gen-l10n (it is not in the template's resource list, so no method is generated) — the l10n test guards this by asserting every key here is a subset of the template's."
}
